                        <provenance type="found" when="1851">Discovered in 1851 by G. V. du Noyer. Found acting as inner lintel of the upper window in the west gable of the ruin of Seskinan parish church (Macalister 1945, 287). The lintel and surrounding gable wall underwent stabilisation work by Tom Pollard and his team between 2018 and 2019 as part of the Knockboy Conservation Project, thanks to funding and support from the Heritage Office at Waterford County Council, the Heritage Council, the National Monuments Service and the Adopt a Monument Scheme. </provenance>
                        <provenance type="observed">Still in place above the upper window in the west gable of the church at Knockboy. This and the six other ogham stones on site were recorded in 3d using photogrammetry by Simon Dowling.
                        </provenance>
