        <body>
             <div type="edition" subtype="ogham" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="pgl-Ogam" resp="#POC">              
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1" style="text-direction:up"/><persName><name nymRef="#?">ᚉᚔᚏ</name> <w type="formula" lemma="maqqas">ᚋᚐᚊᚔ</w> <w>ᚋᚒᚉ<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="stroke"/></w></persName>
                </ab> 
            </div>                    
            <div type="edition" subtype="transliteration" xml:lang="pgl-Ogam" xml:space="preserve" resp="#POC">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1" style="text-direction:up"/><persName><name nymRef="#?">CIR</name> <w type="formula" lemma="maqqas">MAQI</w> <w>MUC<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="stroke"/></w></persName>
                </ab>
                <ab type="list">CIR MAQI MUC[---]</ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp>
                    <app n="1">
                        <note>The presence of MAQI in the inscription suggests that the inscription might have conformed to the commemmorative X son of Y formula.</note>
                    </app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation">
                <p>... son of ...</p> 
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>The inscription contains the common formula word MAQI related to <distinct xml:lang="sga"><ref target="https://dil.ie/31166">mac, macc</ref></distinct> 'son'.</p>
            </div>
